Description: PRS Stripped 58 57/08 PickupsTobacco Burst finish Mahogany neck and bodyPattern neck carve, Rosewood Fretboard Phase III tunersBirds InlayOriginal hardshell Case Stunning looking and sounding example of a classic single cut. Beautiful resonance to it with the V12 finish. Comfortable neck profile. Killer vintage voiced 57/08 pickups... sounds and plays incredible. This axe has a tobacco sunburst / McCarty reddish brown finish and back.Originally offered as a limited run for Experience PRS 2011, the "Stripped" 58 is now available as part of Paul Reed Smith Guitars' Core lineup. The "Stripped" 58 is a no-frills take on the company's popular SC 58 model, which won the Musikmeese International Press Award (mipa) for "Best Electric Guitar 2011/2012" and maintains that instrument's classic, resonant voice that is eminently recordable and gig ready.The "Stripped" 58 is a vintage-inspired instrument that is perfect for more traditional single-cutaway style players and is also instantly comfortable to musicians who grew up playing short scale guitars. Specifications include a flamed curly maple top, mahogany back, 24.5" scale length, 22 fret mahogany "Pattern" neck carve with rosewood fretboard... this axe has the bird inlay option, 57/08 treble and bass pickups with volume and tone control for each pickup and a 3-way toggle on the upper bout. This guitar also features PRS's two piece bridge, which has added weight and mass, creating more contact points that, in turn, create a more resonant, musical instrument."STRIPPED" 58 MODEL SPECS:BODYTop Wood: Flamed MapleBack Wood: MahoganyFinish: V12NECKNumber of Frets: 22Scale Length: 24.5"Neck Wood: MahoganyFretboard Wood: RosewoodFretboard Inlays: Upgraded optional BirdsNeck Shape: PatternWIDTH OF THE FRETBOARD AT THE NUT:Pattern- 1 11/16"WIDTH AT THE BODYPattern - 2 1/4NECK DEPTH AT THE NUTPattern - 27/32"HARDWARE/ELECTRONICSBridgePRS Two Piece BridgeTunersPRS Phase III Locking TunersTruss Rod Cover: BlankHardware Type: NickelTreble Pickup: 57/08 TrebleBass Pickup: 57/08 BassPickup SwitchingVolume and Tone Control for Each Pickup with 3-Way Toggle On Upper BoutOnly 3 discernible things on the guitar :1. a pencil tip sized finish chip on back body edge pictured 2. front top edge binding finish chip, pictured 3. a very small single spot of worming on the back 1/2 inch long so subtle I couldn't catch it in photo.No breaks, warps, repairs, or anything fishy
